# Group General
## General Endpoints [/]

### Deprecated Get Dictionaries [GET /gen/system_dictionary]
API for Services and Dictionaries.

Each dictionary is an object that contains {key}:{value} pairs where: {key} is a dictionary record and {value} is a dictionary record description.

+ Parameters
+ `name` (string, required) - identifier
+ `is_active` (string, required) - identifier

+ Request (application/json)
+ Headers
X-Custom-PSK: a2aa05c76f3f2d91870f923a53cc8aa8f23bbc01a8238d1c2c26d4299715a7e4

+ Response 200 (application/json)
+ Attributes (Response_OK)

+ data (array[Dictionary])

+ Response 400 (application/json)

### PIS Get Dictionaries V2 [GET /gen/system_dictionary]
Each dictionary is an object that contains not only a code and description of a value,
but also a status of the value. In addition, it can represent hierarchical dictionaries with subordinate (child) values

NOTE:

On all envoronments this endpoint DOESN'T require authentication with address:read scope.

+ Parameters
+ `name` (string, required) - identifier
+ `is_active` (string, required) - identifier
+ `value_code` (string, required) - identifier
+ `value_description` (string, required) - identifier
+ `value_is_active` (string, required) - identifier

+ Response 200 (application/json)
+ Attributes (Response__Process_OK)

+ data (array[Dictionary_v2])
    + (object)
        + include Dictionary_v2
        + name (string) - eHealth/ICPC2/condition_codes - Unique dictionary name
        + description (string) - Коди станів за ICPC2 - dictionary description for a user
        + values (array, required)
            + (Dictionary_value)
                + code (string) - D88 - code of the dictionary value
                + description (string) - Апендицит - description of the code

